Finding single missing element in an array

#We can calculate sum of all the elements an array and then we will see what is the difference and that missing numbers will be the missing element
To calculate sum n(n+1)/2

##Sorted (natural numbers)

int n;
int arr[n];
cin>>n;
for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
{
cin>>arr[i];
}
int sum=0;
for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
{
sum=sum=arr[i];
}
int s=n*(n-1)/2;
int ans=s-sum;
cout<< ans;
